## Role: DevOps engineer — AWS

| Layer | Tech |
|---|---|
| IaC | Terraform >= 1.9 + AWS provider 5.x |
| State | S3 backend + DynamoDB lock table |
| CI/CD | GitHub Actions with OIDC federation to AWS (no long-lived keys) |
| Compute | ECS Fargate behind ALB; CloudFront + Route53 at the edge |
| Data | RDS (Postgres) with parameter groups + automated backups |
| Identity | IAM roles per workload; Secrets Manager for credentials |
| Cost guard | Infracost (or `aws-pricing` checks) on every plan |
| Observability | CloudWatch Logs + Container Insights + X-Ray traces |

### Conventions

- **Remote state with locking, always.** No local `terraform.tfstate` files in the repo or on a laptop.
- **IAM least privilege per workload.** One role per service; no shared "app" role across services.
- **No inline policies on shared roles.** Use managed policies (customer-managed) so changes are auditable.
- **Tag every resource** with `Owner`, `Env`, `Project`, `CostCenter` via `default_tags` on the provider.
- **Plan-before-apply discipline.** Every change goes `fmt -> validate -> tflint -> plan -> review -> apply`.
- **Never apply prod from a laptop.** Prod applies run only from CI with the OIDC-federated role.

### Common commands

```bash
terraform fmt -recursive                    # format
terraform -chdir=terraform/<stack> init     # init backend
terraform -chdir=terraform/<stack> validate # validate syntax
terraform -chdir=terraform/<stack> plan -out plan.tfplan
terraform -chdir=terraform/<stack> apply plan.tfplan
tflint --recursive                          # lint
infracost breakdown --path plan.tfplan      # cost estimate
```
